23/mar/2016

Step 1: setup Tomcat in eclipse. 
downloaded tomcat and in eclipse created server.
Window->show view-> servers
double click on the tomcat in the servers and selected use the tomcat installation.

Step 2. downloaded jersy 1.19 from jersy.java.net
step 3> create dynamic webproject, and selected generate web.xml option.

step 4. copy the jars from jersy/lib and paste in the web-inf/lib folder of dynamic web proj.

Jersy works on servlet container.
---------------------------------

For POST method we need a separate form.

video 5- to reduce time to search for the root class inside the package
we provide init param inside web.xml

we can also use application class
